source('C:/Users/ferrariof/Documents/GitHub/FFspatial/R/PRindex_raster.R')
source('C:/Users/ferrariof/Documents/GitHub/FFspatial/R/PRindex.R')



trssf<-sf::st_read('C:/Users/ferrariof/Documents/DFO-Godbout-2020-localSDM/GIS/godbout-fall2020.gpkg', layer='transects')

## Reading layer `transects' from data source `C:\Users\ferrariof\Documents\DFO-Godbout-2020-localSDM\GIS\godbout-fall2020.gpkg' using driver `GPKG'
## Simple feature collection with 8 features and 2 fields
## Geometry type: POLYGON
## Dimension:     XY
## Bounding box:  xmin: 594124 ymin: 5461719 xmax: 595632.8 ymax: 5461896
## Projected CRS: WGS 84 / UTM zone 19N

sbs_vect<-sf::st_read('C:/Users/ferrariof/Documents/DFO-Godbout-2020-localSDM//GIS/godbout-fall2020.gpkg', layer='segmentation_refined')

## Reading layer `segmentation_refined' from data source `C:\Users\ferrariof\Documents\DFO-Godbout-2020-localSDM\GIS\godbout-fall2020.gpkg' using driver `GPKG'
## Simple feature collection with 8109 features and 2 fields
## Geometry type: MULTIPOLYGON
## Dimension:     XY
## Bounding box:  xmin: 594124 ymin: 5461719 xmax: 595632.8 ymax: 5461896
## Projected CRS: WGS 84 / UTM zone 19N

rcksf<-sf::st_cast(sbs_vect[sbs_vect$class_corrected=='rock',], 'POLYGON')

## Warning in st_cast.sf(sbs_vect[sbs_vect$class_corrected == "rock", ], "POLYGON"): repeating attributes for all sub-geometries for which they may not be constant

new<-sf::st_buffer(sf::st_centroid(trssf[1,]), dist=2)

## Warning in st_centroid.sf(trssf[1, ]): st_centroid assumes attributes are constant over geometries of x

n<-5
res<-data.frame(time=NA,fun=rep(c('met','ras'),each =n))

for (i in 1:n){
ras<-system.time(
    mt1<-PRindex_raster(obs_polygon=new, side.cell=0.1,poly=rcksf, buffer=1, zero_distance=0.01) 
)

met<-system.time(
    r1<-met2raster(obs_polygon=new, side.cell=0.1, PRindex,make_spatstat_im=TRUE,poly=rcksf, buffer=1, zero_distance=0.01) 
)

res[c(i,i+n),]$time<-c(met[3],ras[3])

}

res$fun<-as.factor(res$fun)
tapply(res$time, res$fun, mean)

##     met     ras 
## 468.798 418.044

tapply(res$time, res$fun, sd)/sqrt(n)

##      met      ras 
## 31.32064 23.20458

t.test(res$time[1:n],res$time[(n+1):nrow(res)])

## 
##  Welch Two Sample t-test
## 
## data:  res$time[1:n] and res$time[(n + 1):nrow(res)]
## t = 1.3021, df = 7.3745, p-value = 0.2321
## alternative hypothesis: true difference in means is not equal to 0
## 95 percent confidence interval:
##  -40.47851 141.98651
## sample estimates:
## mean of x mean of y 
##   468.798   418.044

boxplot(res$time[1:n],res$time[(n+1):nrow(res)])
